This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and their generalization performance, specifically in the context of Hypothesis Transfer Learning (HTL). The paper discusses the theoretical aspects of HTL and its impact on generalization, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auxiliary hypotheses in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks, which makes these sub-categories likely as well. The paper also discusses the use of regularizers, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS) fields.
